# Architecture

## Layers (Clean-style)

- **Presentation** (UI/API) → **Application** (use cases/services) → **Domain** (entities/rules) → **Infrastructure** (DB, external APIs).
- Dependencies point **inward** — domain does not import from infrastructure.

## By project size (from `TECH_CARD` / `99-project-size.mdc`)

- **A (small):** `src/app`, `components`, `lib`, `types` — simple tree.
- **B (medium):** `features/*` with `components`, `hooks`, `services`, `types`; `shared/` for UI and utils.
- **C (large):** `apps/*`, `packages/*` monorepo; shared UI and domain packages.

## Feature modules

- Public API via `index.ts` — export only what other features need. No deep imports into internal paths.
- **features/X** may depend on **shared**; **shared** must not depend on **features**. Cross-feature deps only when explicit and documented.

## Patterns

- **Composition over inheritance** for UI/logic.
- **Dependency inversion** — inject abstractions (interfaces) for payments, mail, storage.

## Checklist

- [ ] Folder layout matches declared project size
- [ ] No circular imports between features
- [ ] No SQL or server-only secrets in client components
